sbmlme

Class MESBOLPlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbmlme.MESBOLPlugin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MEConstants

    public class MESBOLPlugin
extends java.lang.Object
implements MEConstants
    implements methods to add sequences with additional information to an external SBOL document. This class is intended to reduce the file size of the SBML model while ensuring that the resulting SBOL document follows a schema that can be interpreted by the SBMLme converter.
    Author:
    Marc A. Voigt

      • createSBOLSequenceWithAnnotation

        public void createSBOLSequenceWithAnnotation(org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLDocument sbol,
                                             java.lang.String id,
                                             java.lang.String sequence,
                                             java.lang.String role,
                                             org.sbolstandard.core2.OrientationType ori)
                                      throws org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException
        Create and add a sequence with type and position specific data to the SBOL document.

        This method creates a new sequence object in the SBOL document and then adds this to a newly created ComponentDefinition. A SequenceAnnotation object will be created with position specific data.

        Parameters:
        sbol - the SBOL document
        id - the id of the reaction/species that the sequence belongs to
        sequence - the nucleotide sequence
        role - the type of molecule that the sequence encodes, e.g. "mRNA", "DNA",...
        ori - the orientation of the sequence on the genome
        Throws:
        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException

      • createSBOL

        public void createSBOL(org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLDocument sbol,
                       java.lang.String id,
                       java.lang.String sequence,
                       java.lang.String role)
                throws org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException
        Create and add a sequence to the SBOL document.

        This method creates a new sequence object in the SBOL document and then adds this to a newly created ComponentDefinition. This method is intended to be used for adding sequence information that does not require position or type specific data.

        Parameters:
        sbol - the SBOL document
        id - the id of the reaction/species that the sequence belongs to
        sequence - the nucleotide sequence
        role - the type of molecule that the sequence encodes, e.g. "mRNA", "DNA",...
        Throws:
        org.sbolstandard.core2.SBOLValidationException
